records.addlTxt:
Defendant Antonio Lavell Perkins in court with attorney Annamarie A. Wineke.  Defendant Antonio Lavell Perkins in custody.  Jeremy R. Arn appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, and defendant. 
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 4 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE to any other time being served with credit for 5 days. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 2 YEARS.

The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program AFTER SERVING THE FIRST YEAR OF THIS SENTENCE.  

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 4 YEARS with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Serve 5 months in the House of Correction with release for day reporting center for treatment, job search, and employment; 
*Obtain AODA assessment and if necessary complete follow-up care/treatment;
*Cooperate with random urine screens;
*No illegal drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers/houses);
*Cooperate with all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*No contact with victim Longino H. and his family;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school with part time employment;
*Perform 75 hours of community service;
*Participate in Cognitive Thinking program;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample if not previously done so- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs as to this case and 14CF978 by the end of probation period- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment;

State in compliance with victim rights legislation.  The Court ordered restitution in the stipulated amount of $3,000 payable to Longino H. by the end of probation period- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.  Restitution ordered joint and several with co-actors James Perkins (14CF281) and Joshua Ritchie (14CF282).  If revoked, the Court ordered all financial obligations and restitution to be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.  Defendant is informed he may not possess and/or own any firearms.  Defendant is informed he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been reinstated.  Appeal rights given. 
Filed;
